*-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Molecule: H2O
* Basis: ANO-L-MB and ANO-L-VDZP
* Symmetry: C1
* Features tested: SEW(inline),SCF,RASSCF,SLAPAF, MCKINLEY, EXPBAS
* Responsible person: R. Lindh (2014-02-10)
* Comments: Expand using orbitals, geometry and Hessian in the 2nd step.
*-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*>>> export MOLCAS_REDUCE_PRT=NO
 &Gateway
  Basis set
  H.ANO-L-MB
  H1             -0.83485   0.00000  -0.54410 angstrom
  H2              0.83485   0.00000  -0.54410 angstrom
  End of basis
  Basis set
  O.ANO-L-MB
  O               0.00000   0.00000   0.14286 angstrom
  End of basis
  NoCD
>>> Do While
  &SEWARD
  &RASSCF
     Title=water
     NACTEL=8 0 0
     Inactive=1
     Ras2=6
     Symmetry=1
     Spin=1
  &Alaska
  &SLAPAF
>>>End Do
  &Mckinley

>>>Copy $Project.RunFile RUNFIL1
>>>Copy $Project.RunFile $Project.RunOld

&Gateway
  Basis set
  H.ANO-L-VDZP
  H1             -0.83485   0.00000  -0.54410 angstrom
  H2              0.83485   0.00000  -0.54410 angstrom
  End of basis
  Basis set
  O.ANO-L-VDZP
  O               0.00000   0.00000   0.14286 angstrom
  End of basis
  NoCD

>>>Copy $Project.RunFile RUNFIL2
 &EXPBAS
   FileOrb = $Project.RasOrb
>>> Do While
  &SEWARD
  &RASSCF
     Title=water
     FileOrb = $Project.ExpOrb
     NACTEL=8 0 0
     Inactive=1
     Ras2=6
     Symmetry=1
     Spin=1
     LumOrb
  &Alaska
  &SLAPAF
>>>End Do

